5000|$|The National Wine Centre of Australia (commonly the [...] "Wine Centre") is {{a public}} {{exhibition}} building about winemaking and its industry in South Australia, opened in 2001. It contains an interactive permanent exhibition of winemaking, introducing visitors to the technology, varieties and styles of wine. It also has a <b>wine</b> <b>tasting</b> area, giving visitors the opportunity <b>to</b> <b>taste</b> and compare <b>wines</b> from different areas of Australia.|$|R
